'''俄羅斯烤肉'''（{{lang-ru|Шашлык}}，{{lang-uk|Шашлик}}）是一種主要流行在俄羅斯和烏克蘭等前蘇聯國家的烤肉吃法，类似于[[中东烤肉|中东烤肉]]。这道菜早期在[[高加索|高加索]]和[[中亚|中亚]]地区有其他名称，<ref name="Pokhlebkin_cuisines" /><ref name="Culture and Life 1982" />19世纪起以名称''shashlik''盛行于[[俄罗斯帝国|俄罗斯帝国]]和后来的[[苏联|苏联]]与[[俄罗斯联邦|俄罗斯联邦]]。<ref name="Kraig & Taylor Sen 2013">{{cite book|first1=Bruce|last1=Kraig|first2=Colleen|last2=Taylor Sen|title=Street Food around the World: An Encyclopedia of Food and Culture: An Encyclopedia of Food and Culture|pages=64, 294–295, 384–385|quote=An ancient dish, well known to herders and nomads across a wide swath of the Caucasus and Central Asia, ''shashlyk'' became popular in Russia in the mid-19th century after Georgia, Azerbaijan, and part of Armenia were absorbed into the Russian Empire. In those regions, shashlyk originally referred to cubes of grilled lamb cooked on skewers, whereas basturma was the grilled beef version of this dish. But Russians have broadened the term shashlyk to mean any kind of meat–pork, beef, lamb, venison–cut into cubes, marinated for several hours, threaded onto skewers, and cooked over hot coals.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9XCjAQAAQBAJ|publisher=ABC-CLIO|date=9 September 2013|isbn=9781598849554|via=Google Books|access-date=2022-03-20|archive-date=2020-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200622141912/https://books.google.com/books?id=9XCjAQAAQBAJ}}</ref><ref name="Oxford Companion">{{cite book|last=Davidson|first=Alan|editor-last=Jaine|editor-first=Tom|title=The Oxford Companion to Food|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bIIeBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA442|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|year=2014|pages=442|isbn=9780191040726|via=Google Books|access-date=2022-03-20|archive-date=2022-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220413002013/https://books.google.com/books?id=bIIeBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA442}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|first1=Ken|last1=Albala|title=Food Cultures of the World Encyclopedia|pages=V3:51, V4:35, V4:304|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NTo6c_PJWRgC&pg=RA2-PA51|publisher=ABC-CLIO|date=2011|isbn=9780313376269|via=Google Books|access-date=2022-03-20|archive-date=2020-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114140801/https://books.google.com/books?id=NTo6c_PJWRgC&pg=RA2-PA51}}</ref>

==词源和历史==
''shashlik''（或 ''shashlick''）源于[[突厥语族|突厥语族]]，经由[[俄语|俄语]]''shashlyk''传入英文。<ref name="AH Dictionary">{{Cite web |url=https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=shashlik |title=American Heritage Dictionary Entry: shashlik |access-date=2021-12-01 |archive-date=2022-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415234923/https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=shashlik }}</ref>在突厥族语言中，''shish'' 一词意为“串肉扦”，''shishlik'' 则直译为“可以串在串肉扦上的（东西）”。这个词由[[札波羅結哥薩克|札波羅結哥薩克]]人由{{lang-crh|"şış"}}（“[[烤肉扦|烤肉扦]]”）生造，于18世纪传入俄语，从此便传播到英语及其他欧洲语言。<ref name="Pokhlebkin_cuisines">{{cite book | last = Pokhlebkin | first = William Vasilyevich | author-link = William Pokhlebkin | title = Natsionalnye kukhni nashikh narodov | trans-title = National Cuisines of Our Peoples | script-title  = ru:(Национальные кухни наших народов) | year = 2004 | orig-year = 1978 | publisher = Tsentrpoligraf | location = Moskva | language=ru | isbn = 5-9524-0718-8 }}</ref><ref name="Culture and Life 1982">{{cite book|title=Culture and Life|quote=俄语中的''shashlik''一词来源很是有趣：这个词看起来很像是借自高加索语言之一。可实际上并不是，它的格鲁吉亚语是''mtsvadi''，阿塞拜疆语是''kebab''，而亚美尼亚语是 ''[[Khorovats|horovts]]''。 Shashlik这个词由[[札波羅結哥薩克|札波羅結哥薩克]]由克里米亞韃靼語：''sheesh''（烤肉扦）生造，于18世纪在[[Burkhard_Christoph_von_Münnich|Field-Marshal Mienich]]的[[第四次俄土战争|第四次俄土战争]]后传入俄语，从此便传播到英语及其他欧洲语言。在18世纪之前，这道菜叫 ''verchenoye''，衍生自 ''vertel''，烤肉扦。|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BUwtAQAAMAAJ&q=mtsvadi|publisher=Union of Soviet Societies for Friendship and Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries|date=1982|via=Google Books|access-date=2021-12-01|archive-date=2022-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327221612/https://books.google.com/books?id=BUwtAQAAMAAJ&q=mtsvadi}}</ref><ref name=starling-1>{{cite web|url=http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?root=/usr/local/share/starling/morpho&morpho=1&basename=%5Cusr%5Clocal%5Cshare%5Cstarling%5Cmorpho%5Cvasmer%5Cvasmer&first=17017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080116060559/http://starling.rinet.ru:80/cgi-bin/response.cgi?root=/usr/local/share/starling/morpho&morpho=1&basename=%5Cusr%5Clocal%5Cshare%5Cstarling%5Cmorpho%5Cvasmer%5Cvasmer&first=17017 |archive-date=16 January 2008 |title=Vasmer's Etymological Dictionary |website=starling.rinet.ru|access-date=10 May 2017}}</ref> 在那之前，串在串肉扦上烹调的肉类俄语名称为 ''verchenoye''，衍生自 ''vertel''，“烤肉扦”。<ref name="Culture and Life 1982" />直到19世纪后期之前俄罗斯烤肉都没有传到莫斯科。<ref>Владимир Гиляровский. ''Москва и москвичи'', гл. [[:ru:s:Москва_и_москвичи_(Гиляровский)/Трактиры|Трактиры]].  1926 ([[Vladimir_Gilyarovsky|Vladimir Gilyarovsky]]. ''[[Moscow_and_Muscovites|Moscow and Muscovites]]''. 1926)</ref>自此，它便广受欢迎：到1910年代，它在[[圣彼得堡|圣彼得堡]]的饭店中已成为主要菜品；而到1920年代，它已在全俄罗斯的市区成为常见的街头小吃。

==制作==
[[File:Stamps_of_Tajikistan,_059-02.jpg|thumb]]“东方巴扎”邮票，图案是一位正在烤架上烤俄罗斯烤肉的老人]]
[[File:Shashlik._Armenia.jpg|thumb]]的俄罗斯烤肉]]

最早的俄罗斯烤肉由[[羊肉|羊肉]]制成，但直到现在基于当地习惯或[[宗教法|宗教规定]]，也可由[[豬肉|猪肉]]、[[牛肉|牛肉]]或[[鹿肉|鹿肉]]制成。<ref name="Kraig & Taylor Sen 2013" /><ref name=Pokhlyobkin_Dict>''[http://www.langet.ru/html/q/qaql3k.html Шашлык] {{Wayback|url=http://www.langet.ru/html/q/qaql3k.html |date=20200920115714 }}''. In: В. В. Похлёбкин, ''Кулинарный словарь от А до Я''. Москва, Центрполиграф, 2000, {{ISBN|5-227-00460-9}} ([[William_Pokhlyobkin|William Pokhlyobkin]], ''Culinary Dictionary''. Moscow, Tsentrpoligraf, 2000; Russian)</ref>扦子上可能只有肉，还可能瘦肉、肥肉、蔬菜相间，如[[菜椒|菜椒]]、[[洋蔥|洋葱]]、[[蘑菇|蘑菇]]、[[番茄|番茄]]。在伊朗菜肴中，俄罗斯烤肉所用的肉（相对于其他形式的[[中东烤肉|中东烤肉]]）通常是很大的块，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chn.ir/NSite/FullStory/News/?Id=105446&Serv=0&SGr=0 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-10-12 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012183457/http://www.chn.ir/NSite/FullStory/News/?Id=105446&Serv=0&SGr=0 |archive-date=2013-10-12 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sobhtoos.ir/political/88-%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D9%86%DB%8C-%D9%87%D8%A7/30597-6lik.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-10-12 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012203426/http://sobhtoos.ir/political/88-%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D9%86%DB%8C-%D9%87%D8%A7/30597-6lik.html |archive-date=2013-10-12 }}</ref>而其他地方多用中等大小的肉粒。肉类在烤制之前需要在较高酸度的酱汁中腌制一夜，如添加洋葱、香料的醋、干葡萄酒或酸味水果/[[蔬菜汁|蔬菜汁]]。<ref>[http://www.russlandjournal.de/en/recipes/grilling-and-bbq.html Marinade recipes for shashlik] {{Wayback|url=http://www.russlandjournal.de/en/recipes/grilling-and-bbq.html |date=20080215135153 }} at RusslandJournal.de</ref>{{better source needed|reason=商业网站上的菜谱集合，可能够全面可信|date=2022年3月}}

虽然如今俄罗斯烤肉在饭店的菜单上并不罕见，但它在很多区域更经常由街边摊贩在装有木头、[[木炭|木炭]]或煤炭的烤架上以快餐形式出售。这种烤肉也在露天集会上制作，类似于英语国家的[[烧烤|烧烤]]。

